The paper proposes a learning-based approach to scene parsing using a deep feed-forward neural network, which is a common technique in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also analyzes the learning of the network parameters and proposes modifications to improve performance, which falls under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of an MRF to model hierarchical dependency in the output also suggests a connection to probabilistic graphical models (cs.NE) and natural language processing (cs.CL).
